<p><strong>Users’ data</strong></p>
<p>Our Service allows users to upload, and store information, research data, or other material, perform analyses on it, and download results. Additionally, MuGVRE allows to access selected public data repositories. </p>
<p>User’s data and results obtained (since they are generated automatically without MuG’s human intervention) are treated as confidential and remain the intellectual property of the user.</p>
<p>User’s data is held in a private virtual workspace. Unless agreed in other terms, users’ workspace is limited to 2GB storage size, and is maintained until termination of users’ relationship with MuG. For unregistered users, data is held 10 days after the last connection. For registered users, in case of long term inactivity (2 months), MuG reserves the right to archive users’ data and release the used storage. </p>
<p>Data held in the workspace is only accessible by its owner, although MuG operations staff may be requested to access it to solve eventual operational issues. When necessary, a confidentiality agreement may be formalized. It is the responsibility of the user to ensure that the required agreement is in place prior to uploading any confidential data. </p>
<p>Backup of users’ data is performed periodically following the internal policies of the hosting institutions. MuGVRE or the hosting institutions cannot be held liable for data loss in users’ workspace. Users are advised to keep a local copy of any data uploaded or produced by MuGVRE.</p>
